p: Vaccination induced in calves neutralizing antibodies to A/Argentina/2001 FMDV as early as 7 dpv ( Fig. 1). The vaccinated and IN-challenged calves had a higher mean titer than vaccinated and contact exposed calves from 7 dpi on at each bleeding time, although observed differences were no significant (P > 0.05). The kinetics of neutralizing antibodies of each group is shown in Fig. 1.
